Sentencas: The O-2 reduction reactions on Sr-doped LaMnO3 (LSM) electrodes in solid-oxide fuel cells in the absence and presence of a chromia-forming alloy metallic interconnect have been investigated.
Titulo: Deposition of chromium species at Sr-doped LaMnO3 electrodes in solid oxide fuel cells -: II.: Effect on O2 reduction reaction

Sentencas: Similar to those in the absence of the chromia-forming alloy, the O-2 reduction reactions on LSM electrodes in the presence of chromia-forming alloys are limited by two electrode processes, the diffusion of oxygen species on the LSM surface and the migration of oxygen ions into zirconia electrolyte.
Titulo: Deposition of chromium species at Sr-doped LaMnO3 electrodes in solid oxide fuel cells -: II.: Effect on O2 reduction reaction

Sentencas: In the presence of chromia;forming alloy, the dissociative adsorption and diffusion of oxygen on the LSM electrode surface are inhibited by the gaseous Cr species (e.g.:, CrO3), and the migration processes of oxygen ions into zirconia electrolyte are inhibited by the solid Cr species [e.g., Cr2O3/(Cr, Mn)(3)O-4] deposited on the electrolyte surface.
Titulo: Deposition of chromium species at Sr-doped LaMnO3 electrodes in solid oxide fuel cells -: II.: Effect on O2 reduction reaction

Sentencas: The inhibiting effect of the solid Cr species becomes increasingly dominant on the O-2 reduction with the polarization time.
Titulo: Deposition of chromium species at Sr-doped LaMnO3 electrodes in solid oxide fuel cells -: II.: Effect on O2 reduction reaction

Sentencas: The mechanism and kinetics of the O-2 reduction on the LSM electrodes in the absence and presence of chromia-forming alloy are discussed.
Titulo: Deposition of chromium species at Sr-doped LaMnO3 electrodes in solid oxide fuel cells -: II.: Effect on O2 reduction reaction
